The probability of getting two balls of the same color is the probability of getting two red balls plus the probability of getting two blue balls.

P(same color) = P(both red) + P(both blue)

P(both red) = (8/15) × (x/(x+9))

P(both blue) = (7/15) × (9/(x+9))

So:
