Solution: I need to find the percentage of patients with regular heartbeat and low blood pressure.

Let me define events:
- H = high blood pressure (16%)
- N = normal blood pressure
- L = low blood pressure (19%)
- I = irregular heartbeat (17%)
- R = regular heartbeat

Given information:
- P(H) = 0.16
- P(L) = 0.19
- P(I) = 0.17
- P(H|I) = 0.35
- P(I|N) = 0.11

First, I'll find P(N):
P(H) + P(N) + P(L) = 1
0.16 + P(N) + 0.19 = 1
P(N) = 0.65

Now I'll use the relationship P(I|N) = 0.11:
P(I ∩ N) = P(I|N) × P(N) = 0.11 × 0.65 = 0.0715

Next, I'll find P(H|I) = 0.35:
P(H ∩ I) = P(H|I) × P(I) = 0.35 × 0.17 = 0.0595

Now I can find P(L ∩ I):
P(I) = P(H ∩ I) + P(N ∩ I) + P(L ∩ I)
0.17 = 0.0595 + 0.0715 + P(L ∩ I)
P(L ∩ I) = 0.17 - 0.0595 - 0.0715 = 0.039

Now I need P(R ∩ L):
P(L) = P(L ∩ I) + P(L ∩ R)
0.19 = 0.039 + P(L ∩ R)
P(L ∩ R) = 0.19 - 0.039 = 0.151

Converting to percentage:
0.151 × 100 = 15.1%

Summary: The final answer is $15.1$
