$$L_s = \hbar \times \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}$$

$$L_s = 1.0546 \times 10^{-34} \times 0.8660$$

$$L_s = 9.13 \times 10^{-35} \text{ J·s}$$

Converting to units of $10^{-35}$ J·s:
$$L_s = 9.13 \times 10^{-35} \text{ J·s} = 9.13 \text{ (in units of } 10^{-35} \text{ J·s)}$$

